*By authors*.In the proton experiments, the 0.2-GeV and
2.6-GeV beams were monitored by the activation
technique.
High-enriched Cu-samples, 99.6% of Cu-63 and 98.7%
of Cu-65 were used.
*By authors*.In the proton experiments, the 0.2-GeV and
2.6-GeV beams were monitored by the activation
technique.
High-enriched Cu-samples, 99.6% of Cu-63 and 98.7%
of Cu-65 were used.
*By authors*.In the ion experiments, current
transformer was used to monitor the beam.
The sandwich samplex of six 10.5-mm diameter foils
Cu+Cu-Co+Co-Al+Al, were used. In each of the foil pairs
only the second foils, of 0.25-mm, 0.40-mm and 0.10-mm
thickness, respectively, were spectrometered. In such
a manner, the systematic errors arising from recoil
nuclide escape from the samples have been avoided.
